metadata.name: Aeoflu #207
metadata.description:
This broadcast is transmitted to the brains of the humanoid race from the planet Xiurq during hyperspace travel. The algorithm is specifically designed to preserve the cognitive functions of the species during "slow time" and overload. The use of the algorithm by other races has not been studied. Prohibited for use outside specially certified laboratories by intergalactic convention 30292-HD-92 

The idea of this project is infinite motion, but it can be stopped (‚Äúspace‚Äù) and save static image ("s" button)

There are three modes. They are switched by click. Each switch changes the input parameters, so there are quite a few options

!!!Flashing lights seizure warning!!!

metadata.name: Draad #70
metadata.description:
[‚Ä¶]

At some point, the Artificial Intelligence hooked itself up to a mechanical looming machine.

Being its only way of manifesting itself in the physical world, the AI began communicating through it.

The rigid patterns of horizontal and vertical threads turned out to be insufficient for what the AI had to say. And through the network, it branched out. It found a way of manipulating individual threads by attaching itself to a chenille embroidery machine. This seemingly openened up a whole new vocabulary.

Many have tried to communicate back or propose other ways of communicating by attaching multiple digital devices to the network.

It seems to be only interested in threads.

[‚Ä¶]

‚Äì

Draad ("thread", in Dutch) is a responsive generative artwork. Its canonical form is 1:1, but it scales to 2:3 or 3:2 depending on the viewport.

You can append these parameters to the URL:

[?scale=<number>] scale the renderer.
[?width=<number>&height=<number>] set the dimensions.
[?animation=false] skip animating the threads.
[?mode=duotone] activate duotone mode.
[?mode=monotone] activate monotone mode.

Press [control / command + s] or [tap and hold] to save the current frame.
	- in normal mode: PNG file.
	- in duotone mode: SVG file in two colors, suitable for plotting with two pens.
	- in monotone mode: SVG file in black, suitable for plotting with a single pen.

¬© 2022 Monokai.

metadata.name: Garden, Monoliths #248
metadata.description:
"Garden, Monoliths" is the result of an algorithm that started in April 2021. It was called "Grass.js".
Spring was blooming all around the house, taking over the stones and remnants of ancient battles that stood here. Inspiration was everywhere.
The initial goal was to use mathematical formulas for creating patterns inspired by the density of nature, that could be used by a pen plotter, so it kept focusing on outputting vector lines. This history and practice produced a graphical style based on line strokes, plus occasionally some transparent, filled shapes.
Each artwork will be either "Garden" or "Monolith", for they are variations of two existing designs from the workshop.

metadata.name: Furrr #103
metadata.description:
Inspired by natural macro structures, I experimented to create a hairy, soft, tactile surface, using gradient colors and overlays. The curves are an optical illusion, no curved lines are used. 

PS: No animals were hurt during this project:)

Best viewed on desktop

Press s in live mode for a 1414x2000 download

Download a higher resolution by adding to the URL:
&density=2
&density=3
&density=4

Lammetje July 2022

metadata.name: Magic Mushrooms #39
metadata.description:
Magic Mushrooms is an algorithm that generates 1990‚Äôs style random dot autostereogram drawings of psychedelic fungus.  I am not going to attempt to tell you how to see the mushrooms in these drawings.  Instead, you should watch a youtube video about stereograms or get very high with someone who was around in the 90s.

All due props and attribution go to the authors of the open source library stereogram.js, a modified version of which was used in this project to draw a bunch of colored squares in a grid that can trick the brains of some human beings into seeing magic mushrooms.  Like stereogram.js, this project is in no way affiliated with Magic Eye Inc.

Created by @capnganj - one love <3

metadata.name: Modulacions 3: 'Cubes' (audio) #9
metadata.description:
"Modulacions 3: Cubes" is the third piece of the series 'Modulacions' (modulations). 

-NOTE: Headphones recomended. Some extreme sounds (frequency and amplitude) can be generated. (click to start)


-modulation with an oscillator (carrier) with an LFO (modulator).

-The output sound is visualized inside a cube (using 5 of the 6 planes of a cube)

-3 types of modulations: FM, AM and noise-AM.

-From 4 to 12 modulations.

-11 possible visualizations.

-5 possible visualizations-plane combinations 

-all parameters are ramdomly assigned. Not all parameters changes from one modulation to the next one.

Features:

"numModulations": number of diferent modulations
"darkMode": dark mode (true or false)
"modulations": number of different modulations 1-3 (fm, am and noise)
"carrierWaves": number of different waveforms for the carrier 1-4 (sine, square, triangle and sawtooth) 
"modulatorWaves": number of different waveforms for the modulator 1-4 (sine, square, triangle and sawtooth),
"visuals": number of different visual patterns  1-11.
"distVisuals": number of different visual combinations  1-5.

-powered by 5js and p5.sound

metadata.name: Chromatic Waves #217
metadata.description:
Threads of color are weaved together, interacting and vibrating.

SVG generated with JavaScript.

The SVG can be saved by pressing "s" on the full-screen view.
A PNG version can be exported by pressing "e" on the full-screen view.

By default the dimensions of the export are 3200√ó2400.
These dimensions can be changed by adding, for example, ?w=3200&h=1800 to the full-screen page URL, where w is the desired width and h the desired height. Then press "e" to export at this size.

metadata.name: the Horizon #76
metadata.description:
I am interested in and pay attention to repeating patterns in nature. Searching for the possibility of depicting this rhythm, texture, and space opens this opportunity as a new experience for me. And how can I convert time to image? In this work, I have depicted the circle of wandering, like the sun that fluctuates in every horizon and climate, sometimes hot and tense and sometimes its rays like the morning breeze caressing our face, calling us to a new beginning. Where is your sun on the horizon, and what time is it in your world?
Made in p5js
Created July 2022
Artist: @ChistaAi
